-- Lonza Doesn’t Plan Large-Scale Redundancies, NZZ am Sonntag Says
-- B y   D e r m o t   D o h e r t y
-- 2012-04-08T10:47:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-08/lonza-doesn-t-plan-large-scale-redundancies-nzz-am-sonntag-says.html
Lonza Group AG (LONN)  doesn’t plan to cut a
large number of jobs as part of a cost-reduction program,  NZZ am
Sonntag  reported, citing Chairman Rolf Soiron.  While there will be fewer positions, “no one is thinking
of mass redundancies,” Soiron said in an interview in today’s
newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dermot Doherty in Geneva, Switzerland, via 
 ddoherty9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sara Marley at 
 smarley1@bloomberg.net  